      "span_text": "The discovery that fluid flow stimulates TRPM7 incorporation into the plasma membrane was enabled by the novel use of green fluorescent protein (GFP)-tagged TRPM7 in conjunction with total internal reflection fluorescence (TIRF) microscopy, which conferred the ability to visualize translocation of the channel from vesicular structures within the cell.  Consequently this response to flow could only be visualized in cell lines transfected with the GFP construct."
